        <abstract>
            <p>CD’s predicament with continental extensions: they would remove argument for multiple creations, yet he opposes the doctrine. Lyell will not express an opinion on this.</p>
            <p>Lyell fears mutability would lead to more specific names.</p> 
<p>Encloses copy of letters to Lyell [<hi rend="doubleUnderline">1910</hi> and <hi rend="doubleUnderline">1917</hi>].</p> 
